{"parentUuid":"47b07bca-8d44-462d-9efb-510a71b1c6f8","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"e7a5f37c-bbab-455c-993d-372a19a0cd13","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a93c57793cb1d16d4","slug":"snazzy-sparking-torvalds","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J5roe3YJJtatXSdGsT51xL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 733\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/733](https://www.erdosproblems.com/733)\n    23→\n    24→Call a sequence $1 < X_1 \\leq \\cdots \\leq X_m \\leq n$ line-compatible if there is a set of $n$\n    25→points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ such that there are $m$ lines $\\ell_1, \\ldots, \\ell_m$ containing at least\n    26→two points, and the number of points on $\\ell_i$ is exactly $X_i$.\n    27→\n    28→This is essentially the same as problem 607, but with multiplicities. See also problem 732.\n    29→\n    30→Proved by Szemerédi and Trotter [SzTr83].\n    31→\n    32→[Er81] Erdős, P., 1981.\n    33→\n    34→[SzTr83] Szemerédi, E. and Trotter, W. T., _Extremal problems in discrete geometry_.\n    35→Combinatorica 3 (1983), 381–392.\n    36→-/\n    37→\n    38→open Classical\n    39→\n    40→namespace Erdos733\n    41→\n    42→/-- Three points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ are collinear: the cross product of the displacement\n    43→vectors $(q - p)$ and $(r - p)$ vanishes. -/\n    44→def Collinear (p q r : ℝ × ℝ) : Prop :=\n    45→  (q.1 - p.1) * (r.2 - p.2) = (r.1 - p.1) * (q.2 - p.2)\n    46→\n    47→/-- A line determined by a point set $P$: the set of all points in $P$ collinear\n    48→with a given pair of distinct points. -/\n    49→def IsLine (P : Finset (ℝ × ℝ)) (L : Finset (ℝ × ℝ)) : Prop :=\n    50→  L ⊆ P ∧ 2 ≤ L.card ∧\n    51→  ∃ p q : ℝ × ℝ, p ∈ P ∧ q ∈ P ∧ p ≠ q ∧\n    52→    L = P.filter (fun r => Collinear p q r)\n    53→\n    54→/-- A multiset of natural numbers is line-compatible for $n$ if there exists a\n    55→point set $P$ of size $n$ in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ whose collection of determined lines yields\n    56→that multiset of sizes. -/\n    57→def IsLineCompatible (n : ℕ) (M : Multiset ℕ) : Prop :=\n    58→  ∃ P : Finset (ℝ × ℝ), P.card = n ∧\n    59→    ∃ lines : Finset (Finset (ℝ × ℝ)),\n    60→      (∀ L ∈ lines, IsLine P L) ∧\n    61→      (∀ L, IsLine P L → L ∈ lines) ∧\n    62→      lines.val.map Finset.card = M\n    63→\n    64→/-- The set of achievable line-compatible multisets for $n$-point configurations\n    65→in $\\mathbb{R}^2$. -/\n    66→def achievableLineMultisets (n : ℕ) : Set (Multiset ℕ) :=\n    67→  {M | IsLineCompatible n M}\n    68→\n    69→/--\n    70→**Erdős Problem 733** [Er81]:\n    71→\n    72→There exists a constant $C > 0$ such that for all sufficiently large $n$, the number\n    73→of line-compatible sequences (multisets of line sizes from $n$-point configurations\n    74→in $\\mathbb{R}^2$) is at most $\\exp(C \\cdot \\sqrt{n})$.\n    75→\n    76→Proved by Szemerédi and Trotter [SzTr83].\n    77→-/\n    78→@[category research solved, AMS 5 52]\n    79→theorem erdos_733 :\n    80→    ∃ C : ℝ, 0 < C ∧ ∃ n₀ : ℕ, ∀ n : ℕ, n₀ ≤ n →\n    81→      (achievableLineMultisets n).Finite ∧\n    82→      ((achievableLineMultisets n).ncard : ℝ) ≤\n    83→        Real.exp (C * Real.sqrt (n : ℝ)) := by\n    84→  sorry\n    85→\n    86→end Erdos733\n    87→"}]},"uuid":"bec8c84b-b0d4-4a1a-86de-762883262a81","timestamp":"2026-03-10T22:28:32.003Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"47b07bca-8d44-462d-9efb-510a71b1c6f8"}
